&quot;Assertions in the press that our compliance with these [FISA] requests gives the U.S. government unfettered access to our users’ data are simply untrue.&quot;<p>What about the non-FISA requests, has any of them given the U.S. government unfettered access to user data?<p>What does unfettered mean? 
&quot;You only can access all user data for 2 hours&quot; 
